    "sections": {
        "description": "<p>This plugin implements the toolbar for more comfortable post controls. You can enable/disable it from &#8220;Screen Options&#8221; panel.</p>\n<p>Also you can use hotkeys:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Save/update post &#8211; Ctrl + S</li>\n<li>Delete post (move to trash) &#8211; Ctrl + D</li>\n<li>Change status of post &#8211; Ctrl + 1</li>\n<li>Change visibility of post &#8211; Ctrl + 2</li>\n<li>Show revisions &#8211; Ctrl + 3</li>\n<li>Change data of post &#8211; Ctrl + 4</li>\n</ul>\n",
        "installation": "<ol>\n<li>Upload <code>post-editing-toolbar</code> folder to the <code>/wp-content/plugins/</code> directory.</li>\n<li>Activate the plugin through the &#8216;Plugins&#8217; menu in WordPress.</li>\n</ol>\n",
        "changelog": "<h4>0.2</h4>\n<ul>\n<li>Hotkeys support added</li>\n</ul>\n<h4>0.1</h4>\n<ul>\n<li>Initial release</li>\n</ul>\n"
